rComments: Wow.. The class was very entertaining. There's no midterm but ten quizzes instead (she does her best to quietly give you the answer throughout the lectures mainly on Tuesday). Her quizzes are manageable and sometimes quite challenging to say the least. I would definitely go to section as the TAs are awesome at explaining the concept.

Larrabee's lectures are actually entertaining - she makes you want to class. Which is a good thing, because I feel like this class would be very very hard if you don't go to lecture, but is very manageable if you do go to lecture. If you don't understand something, just ask - she'll try her hardest to get it to click. Fantastic teacher!

Awesome teacher, great personality and will keep you entertained. No Midterm, 10 pop quizzes and a cumulative final. All test materials are very fair and straight forward. At time Tracy does rush some material, so don't be lazy and review her lectures and the book on your own. Take good notes and understand the quizzes before you take the final
Good professor, easy weekly quizzes, no midterm

Ms Larrabee is really engaging, funny, and a good teacher. I learned a lot from her. However she was not clear on the content for tests. She would say "Don't worry about this for this weeks quiz" and then it would appear on the quiz anyway. The homework rarely reflected the quizzes, it was mostly the slides, which she doesn't post so take pics

Larrabee is an incredibly passionate teacher, and she really cares about her students and the material. To do well in the class, I would go to MSI, and don't be afraid to ask questions during lecture (in fact, she encourages it)

CE-16 with Larrabee is one of the best classes I have ever taken. The material isn't hard, but a little studying and/or practice is still needed if you want an A. However, professor Larrabee is very straightforward and easy to understand, and genuinely cares about her students. No midterm, but she tells you exactly what to expect on each quiz.

Larrabee is an excellent and engaging lecturer with a passion for teaching. She taught so well, that the class seemed easy despite the material being somewhat difficult! There are weekly quizzes that come from lectures and the homework so it'd be in your best interest to review those! She posts her lectures online as well. Would highly recommend!
Professor Larrabee is one of the most inspirational and gifted professors that I have ever known.  I found her lectures to be clear, informative, and entertaining. I highly recommend her.
Awesome professor. She will honestly work her hardest to make sure students understand. The quiz-a-week structure is way better than the normal midterm structure in my opinion.

Larrabee is absolutely amazing. I went into this class as an business econ major but thanks to this class I've found my passion for computer science. She is so incredibly smart and clear while teaching. Take this class you won't regret it.

She makes it extremely clear how the examples she did in lecture were going to be on the quizzes.  Go to class and do all the examples in the lecture and the quizzes are easy. The online homework was hard to use and many times incorrect but easy to get full credit on.

Weekly labs & quizzes, no midterms, 1 final. Labs were difficult and never based on the quizzes. Whatever she says will be on the quiz is never really on the quiz. The only time she's helpful is the day of the quiz because she starts going over a couple questions that are very similar. Hard to study for quizzes because you don't know what to expect
good

Larrabee was an amazing professor. She is very knowledgeable, so sometimes non-CMPSCMPS students may get lost during lectures, but otherwise she really knows her stuff and is always talking about things going on in the tech world. She would take YouTube video breaks and made the material easy to understand (For tech-people, at least). I recommend.

Tracy is one of the most helpful and caring professors at UCSC. She WANTS to help you and WANTS you to learn the material. No midterm, weekly qiuzzes which are very straight forward. The material for this class can be difficult and majority of the class will be in lab. If you do the labs and put in the time, the grade will reflect. Great professor!
The material itself was not very difficult. Tracy just makes it kind of hard to follow. Not a fun class.

This class was unnecessarily difficult! Tracy just rambles on during lectures and her explanations don't make sense AT ALL. The labs generally have nothing to do with quiz material and are very confusing. I hate this class more than anything. I took this class as a required computer class for bme major, but I wish I'd chosen another computer class.

Hated her. Good class, but I just didn't like her. Sure, she's funny by throwing some teases around every now and then. But when you ask her a question for help/lab/quiz, she gets really arrogant and stuck up. Hated her attitude so much.

Simply horrible of a teacher. Her previous students said the material was simple enough to understand. Well, not for Spring 2013... I didn't know wtf she was lecturing about for the last half of the quarter; went to section and found that more helpful. She cannot teach; just rants on and on and expects you to immediately understand everything.

Classic absent minded prof. She wanders into class late and unprepaired, and blows everyone away with her mastery of the material and desire to teach. Unfortunatly she is very sensitive to students opionons, disparage her and her cat will know about it.
this course was way too much work, but it helped my writing, so maybe it was worth it.
Very Clear and helpful, but not as helpful in the lab.
She was effective teacher and tought in a way that was easy to understand. Lectures were enjoyable as well.
wow..what an utter headcase..I dont understand her  hating the world complex and constant power tripping over all the undergrads
waste of time
She made the class interesting -- I actually looked forward to going to class and she gave us exactly what was going to be on our tests.
I quite enjoyed her class, its better than Tantalo!
Let's see, unprepared, rambles about sexual stuff (obviously not getting any tail), seems rather pissed at the world, and her lectures are impossible to follow. Other than that, a terrific professor.
Horrible, utterly worthless lectures!!! Avoid her like the plague.
Tracy is a great professor, but not because of her lectures. Although frequently unprepared for lecture, she knows her material extremely well and can discuss it like nobody's business.

Larrabee finds the material she is teaching easy and expects everyone to get it. However, the majority of the class were business majors who were unfamiliar with the content. She's definitely enthusiastic and well-verse in her area, but she just can't teach and deliver the content. She is  incredibly smart but she can't teach.

She made easy material super confusing just because a lot of people said her class was easy last quarter. She has major attitude towards students who asks "stupid" questions and really likes to make fun of those who try to understand the material she may think is easy.

I showed up to class but barely paid attention. Every 10 minutes or so, she would diverge from the topic and we would watch a funny youtube video that usually didn't pertain to the course. She's really enthusiastic and she knows her information really well. She teaches well and her tests/quizzes aren't very difficult either.
Super friendly and approachable. Very willing to help students outside of class through the forum/email/skype/any medium that works for the student.

Go to class, do the homework, go to MSI, and you are pretty much guaranteed an A. I have never met a teacher with this much of a passion for teaching. Get her as your professor if you get the chance! BEST teacher I've ever had at UCSC!

If you go to class and do the homework you are guaranteed at least a B.  No midterms just weekly quizzes which she pretty much gives the answers to during lectures.  Very funny teacher, I would definitely take a class with her again.  Loves teaching

Really cool and awesome teacher. Her interest in CS 12 was a lot which you can tell with the way she teaches. It's a tough class, so be prepared to read and do homework, and the labs are just awful, spent 12-14 hours per week doing extremely hard labs. Very nice teacher though and super helpful!

Take her for 80n!!!! Material might be new to you, but she will walk you through everything you need to know for quizzes and final. If you go to class, read the slides and go to 1 section a week, you will get an A. No surprises on quizzes, she will tell u exactly what to study. Ask ?s & use office hours if you need to. Super helpful.No book to buy!
Great teacher, made a really hard class pretty easy. Gives more than enough information and help to pass all the material easily.

Great teacher.  She will go over  any topic or question as many times as necessary.  DO NOT be scared to ask questions in class!  you are never turned away. Funny, is up to date, loves memes and she gives youtube breaks when switching topics.  final was not a mystery at all.  you get the grade you earn.  text book is FREE! don't buy it early.
Awesome teacher, very approachable and willing to help. Go to section, study for quizzes a little, do the hw, and you can get an A

This class does require time. I would not have passed with an A had I not gone to the optional sections regularly. Her TAs usually do a better job of making the material less complicated for students new to the computer science field. However, she really wants you to do well and is willing to go out of her way to help you.Shes also funny

Tracy is one of the most animated professors I have ever had.  She is always trying to figure out ways to teach people certain concepts the most effectively.  It is incredibly easy to do well in her class by doing one simple thing: actually go to class.

Good teacher, definitely puts time and effort into the lectures to make sure the students understand. And will promptly respond to any student having trouble. Tries to keep the class entertaining with jokes and videos, but a lot of them tend to be not funny or just puzzling. Leads to awkward silences...Overall pretty good class though.
shes probably the best professor I had at ucsc. I think its worth it to take the class just to watch her speak. The class for me was inspirational.

Really good teacher really wants students to learn, feel free to ask her any questions, skype, email, forums, one of the smartest and most interesting teachers at UCSC, if the effort is put in the grade will follow, quizzes were super easy as they were RIGHT out of the homework

I must say, I don't really like Larabee. I can see why most students like her, but I found that her lectures were extremely simple against her quizzes, which I thought weren't always fair. I feel like she takes the material too elementary and doesn't really show us the true complexity of CE. Good class for non-CE majors, otherwise, GLHF
Great professor. Takes the time to make sure her students really understand the material. Very energetic in lectures, which are interactive and accessible online. Reasonable grader and person.

Very receptive to student concerns. Very clear and organized. Willing to bend over backwards to help you succeed. She takes a high-tech approach to teaching, encourages laptops in class. She makes the material interesting, and references to geek culture help keep the class fun. Overall outstanding teacher. Sets the standard for other professors.

A pretty good teacher, although not the best. She goes over what happened in the previous lecture. Although she likes to waste time a little bit by playing youtube videos and start the day off with lolcats, those were quite the enjoyable break from most classes. The weekly quizzes werent bad as long as you studied.

Some of the comments seem harsh and not what I have seen from her so far. Very well organized lectures: last lecture recap, onlines slides, open to class discussion and weekly quizzes. The homework does take time but the book is complete and you will learn alot. Tracy is very charismatic, engaging and friendly. I would recommend this class.

Excellent Instructor.  If you need help just ask.  She makes ever effort to make sure you really learn.  If she doesn't know something she will find if out for you.  She's comes across as a human.  Be ready to work hard and do your part.  It will be very rewarding.

The WORST professor at UCSC, hands down, don't take the class! Larrabee can't teach for her life. All we did was watch pointless youtube videos all quarter long. She's also extremely disrespectful toward students, and has a major attitude problem.
I actually like her class she has good attitude

Larrabee's class was fun, as far as discrete mathematics goes. I was kept interested. She and her TAs were very helpful in explaining some difficult concepts personally. Her tests and quizzes are fairly graded. I really can't think of anything bad to say about her!
I learned much more in lab than I did in lecture. Tracy's lectures are much too simple. Easy A, though.
Shes an awesome teacher! Her class was about very boring stuff but she managed to make the time speed by. didn't fall asleep once. I look forward to having her again for another class next qtr

Take her class, and ask as many questions as your heart desires, she will answer them! She is very helpful and will drop everything she is doing if you need to talk to her after class. She is there for you. She is a true mentor and really cares about student progress.  A+ in my book.

More than half of each class was wasted with random stories or diversions. Many times the class felt pointless with how easy it was.  Now that I have taken other classes which require information learned in CMPE 100 I realize I didn't learn the material despite a good grade.

While Tracy had an energetic approach towards this class, her teaching skills are not that good. The lectures were so boring, and if it weren't for her weekly quizzes, no one would ever show up!  The lab portion of the class was quite demanding as well, and the lecture tied in very poorly with the lab!  Her final was freakishly easy!
Clearly dedicated to teaching well and conveying the material.  The best professor I've ever had in any class.
No Comments
Very cool teacher. Definately a little strange, but that Santa Cruz. I learned a lot... you just have to pay really close attention as her train of thought jumps around a lot.

Sometimes I felt like she was teaching to me personally, which can be good or bad (I was embarassed when I didn't feel like I had the material).  I learned a lot.  I feel like I survived, and I'm proud.
I think Tracy was a very cool teacher. She understands that not all people in the class are in the CE major and she structured her class like that.I would take any class of her's again

Tracy is funny and I like her personality. She is definitely very smart and I wonder if people that smart should teach, because they have a hard time relaying complex material to the rest of us. She's willing to help you but I got the impression it was because she had to not because she truly cared.

Tracy is an awesome professor. She is very friendly and very much part of the class during her lectures. She's witty, personable, approachable. She gives very good lectures and I felt very rewarded by having this class with her.
She was a great teacher to have. I felt challenged, but not overwhelmed. Very clear on what you need to know and don't need to know.
The Car is driving but no one is behind the wheels! Good teacher, a littte strange. Funny, easy and cool.

Frequent mistakes in notes but makes you "ride along" with her and you really learn the material. Her lectures are never a bore and don't even sound like lectures. You're just talking about the subject. And when you leave, you realize you've lea
